cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a meta-learning method for adaptively learning hyperparameters in robust loss functions. It also involves training a neural network to handle noisy labels, which is a common task in machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the experiments involve image classification tasks. Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the proposed method involves training a neural network and optimizing loss functions.
